abstract: President Vladimir Putin on Monday opened a rail route linking Russia's two biggest cities to Crimea, which Moscow annexed from Ukraine in 2014, and said it proved that the country could deliver on giant infrastructure projects.
snippet: President Vladimir Putin on Monday opened a rail route linking Russia's two biggest cities to Crimea, which Moscow annexed from Ukraine in 2014, and said it proved that the country could deliver on giant infrastructure projects.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — President Vladimir Putin on Monday opened a rail route linking Russia's two biggest cities to Crimea, which Moscow annexed from Ukraine in 2014, and said it proved that the country could deliver on giant infrastructure projects.
headline_main: Putin Opens Russian Rail Route to Annexed Crimea

abstract: Fantasy sports and gambling company DraftKings will be taken public by an entity founded by Hollywood executives Jeff Sagansky and Harry Sloan in a deal valuing the company $3.3 billion (2.6 billion pounds), the firm said on Monday.
snippet: Fantasy sports and gambling company DraftKings will be taken public by an entity founded by Hollywood executives Jeff Sagansky and Harry Sloan in a deal valuing the company $3.3 billion (2.6 billion pounds), the firm said on Monday.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Fantasy sports and gambling company DraftKings will be taken public by an entity founded by Hollywood executives Jeff Sagansky and Harry Sloan in a deal valuing the company $3.3 billion (2.6 billion pounds), the firm said on Monday.
headline_main: DraftKings to Go Public in 2020 at $3.3 Billion Valuation
headline_print_headline: DraftKings to Go Public in 2020 at $3.3 Billion Valuation

abstract: In the not-so-distant past, TV viewers were forced to wait a week for the next instalment of their favourite shows, parcelled out by networks in half-hour or hour-long increments.

abstract: Newcastle United will assess striker Andy Carroll's fitness before deciding if he can face Manchester United on Thursday but his return from injury has already lifted spirits in the squad, manager Steve Bruce said on Monday.

abstract: Passengers on a tram in Germany forced their way into the cab and stopped the speeding vehicle after the driver passed out and they couldn't get the emergency brake to work.

abstract: The S&P 500 and the Nasdaq hit fresh record highs on Monday as President Donald Trump said an initial U.S.-China trade pact would be signed "very shortly", while Boeing shares lifted the Dow after the planemaker fired its chief executive officer.

abstract: Indian Muslims protesting against a citizenship law which they say is discriminatory are carrying national flags and copies of the constitution, aiming to prevent supporters of the Hindu nationalist government from painting them as anti-India.
snippet: Indian Muslims protesting against a citizenship law which they say is discriminatory are carrying national flags and copies of the constitution, aiming to prevent supporters of the Hindu nationalist government from painting them as anti-India.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI/BENGALURU — Indian Muslims protesting against a citizenship law which they say is discriminatory are carrying national flags and copies of the constitution, aiming to prevent supporters of the Hindu nationalist government from painting them as anti-India.
headline_main: Indian Muslims Wave National Flag to Show Protest Is Not Anti-India
headline_print_headline: Indian Muslims Wave National Flag to Show Protest Is Not Anti-India
